	<text name="AVMC">
		Visuelle Auto-ignorier Einstellungen:

This function will allow you to set a size limit in KB and surface size in m² for objects and avatars,
if an avatat hits the overall surface or size limit, the whole avatar will be visually muted,
your own included, if the whole object or a prim of that object linkset hits the limit the whole object
will be derendered, your HUDs included. Use the Avatar Render Cost option in Usefull Functions to get
an idea about what your and all the other avatars consume in KB/m². 0 = Unlimited.
	</text>
	<text name="AVHC">
		Visuelle Auto-derender Einstellungen (Anti-Sculpt-crash):

This function allows you to set a surface size in m² at which single objects or whole linksets
should be derendered, this is good for sculpt crashers or very expensive single prim/sculpt objects
that might otherwise kill your performance, keep in mind that most objects are pending between
0.1 and 20m² depending on your size and how much textured faces an object has,
meshes will also count towards this, especially rigged meshes will probably hit the 20m² limit fast.
A good default for crash protection therefor is about 100-200m² as it shouldnt derender anything
important but prevents you from seeing those crashers. 0 = Unlimited.
	</text>
